tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE participants (
  participant_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  participant_name VARCHAR(50),
  age INT,
  gender VARCHAR(10),
  study_start_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE Participants (
  participant_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  age INT,
  gender VARCHAR(10),
  contact_number VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE Responses (
  response_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  participant_id INT,
  question VARCHAR(255),
  answer TEXT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE participants (
  participant_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(50),
  age INT,
  gender VARCHAR(10),
  email VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE behaviors (
  behavior_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  participant_id UUID REFERENCES participants(participant_id),
  behavior_type VARCHAR(50),
  behavior_description TEXT,
  behavior_date TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE surveys (
  survey_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  participant_id UUID REFERENCES participants(participant_id),
  survey_question VARCHAR(255),
  survey_response TEXT,
  survey_date TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE Participants (
    participant_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name VARCHAR(50),
    last_name VARCHAR(50),
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10)
);

CREATE TABLE Surveys (
    survey_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    participant_id INT,
    survey_date DATE,
    question1 VARCHAR(255),
    question2 VARCHAR(255),
    question3 VARCHAR(255),
    FOREIGN KEY (participant_id) REFERENCES Participants(participant_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Responses (
    response_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    survey_id INT,
    question_number INT,
    response_text TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (survey_id) REFERENCES Surveys(survey_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Observations (
    observation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    participant_id INT,
    observation_date DATE,
    behavior_description TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (participant_id) REFERENCES Participants(participant_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Participants (
    participant_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    age INT,
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    email VARCHAR(50),
    phone_number VARCHAR(15)
)

CREATE TABLE StudySessions (
    session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    participant_id INT,
    session_date DATE,
    session_time TIME,
    FOREIGN KEY (participant_id) REFERENCES Participants(participant_id)
)

CREATE TABLE Responses (
    response_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    session_id INT,
    question_id INT,
    answer VARCHAR(255),
    FOREIGN KEY (session_id) REFERENCES StudySessions(session_id)
)

CREATE TABLE Questions (
    question_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    question_text TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE Researchers (
    researcher_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    expertise VARCHAR(50)
)
